<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/553021c0667aa14f91cfb02bc51021aa> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Skåne"@sv, "Brösttumörer"@sv, "Breast Neoplasms"@en, "Tumörer"@sv, "Neoplasms"@en, "Blodprovstagning"@sv, "Blood Specimen Collection"@en, "Scania"@en, "EpiHealth"@sv, "EpiHealth"@en, "EpiHealth_Skåne"@sv, "EpiHealth_Skåne"@en, "Plasma"@sv, "Plasma"@en, "Biomarkörer"@sv, "Biomarkers"@en, "DNA"@sv, "DNA"@en, "Serum"@sv, "Serum"@en, "Tumörmark��rer"@sv, "Biomarkers, Tumor"@en, "Paraffininbäddning"@sv, "Paraffin Embedding"@en, "Vävnadsinbäddning"@sv, "Tissue Embedding"@en, "fryst vävnad"@sv, "frozen tissue"@en, "CANCER"@en, "CANCER"@sv;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__49564.
_:b0__49564 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/147462b75fe0ee02053d5d6a5c1977ee>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/553021c0667aa14f91cfb02bc51021aa> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/NON_PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2321000255>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Deltagarna i denna kohort är individer som har drabbats av metastaserande bröstcancer och som sedan 2003 har kommit till onkologen i Lund för behandling. Insamlingen till studien pågår fortfarande. Från alla individer finns det information om status för den primära tumören, metastaslokal, tumörvolym, samt vilken/vilka behandlingar de har genomgått. Det finns även paraffininbäddad primärtumör sparad från alla individer, och för en subgrupp av kohorten har fryst primärtumörvävnad sparats. DNA, plasma och serum finns sparat från samtliga individer.\n\nSyfte:\n\nAtt hitta tumörmarkörer eller tumörceller i blod från patienter med metastaserande bröstcancer.\n\nInsamling i studien startade 2003 och är pågående (antal individer uppgick till drygt 300 år 2010)."@sv, "The participants in this cohort are individuals with breast cancer and metastatic disease coming to the Department of Oncology in Lund for treatment since 2003. The data collection in the study is still ongoing. From all individuals, there is information about the status of the primary tumor, metastatic sites, tumor volume, and treatments. There are also paraffin-embedded tissue from primary tumor saved from all individuals, and for a subset of the cohort also frozen primary tumor tissue saved. There is DNA, plasma and serum saved from all individuals.\n\nPurpose:\n\nTo find tumor markers or tumor cells in the blood from patients with metastatic breast cancer.\n\nData collection was started in 2003 and is ongoing (in 2010 there were over 300 individuals included in the study)."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#contactPoint> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/6dc7158c79867ed5a4f80fb0fefd42cd>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2014-09-05T07:09:52Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2017-03-21T15:36:49Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Bröstcancer- en metastasstudie"@sv, "Breast Cancer-metastases study"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/HEAL>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/temporal> _:b0__50032.
_:b0__50032 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#startDate> "2003"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime>.
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/553021c0667aa14f91cfb02bc51021aa> a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#97dc458e945b429f6e81783bb839ebad>.
<#97dc458e945b429f6e81783bb839ebad> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://doi.org/10.5878/w88z-ta87>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-04-18T06:27:06.187Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#97dc458e945b429f6e81783bb839ebad> {
<https://doi.org/10.5878/w88z-ta87> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "resurser"@sv, "resources"@en, "burnout"@en, "utbrändhet"@sv, "Emotional demands"@en, "Känslomässigt krav"@sv, "HEALTH"@en, "HÄLSA"@sv, "HEALTH PROFESSIONALS"@en, "HÄLSOPERSONAL"@sv, "PUBLIC HEALTH"@en, "FOLKHÄLSA"@sv, "WELL-BEING (HEALTH)"@en, "V��LBEFINNANDE (HÄLSA)"@sv;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__2685.
_:b0__2685 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/8ff7124c06939f282690b2b168f35bde>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/w88z-ta87> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/NON_PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/SWE>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002890>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The dataset was generated within a research project in occupational health science focusing on emotional burdens in working life and their associations with health and well-being. The data material consists of survey data covering emotional demands, emotional labor (including the strategy of deep acting), burnout, and mental well-being, as well as potential protective work-related resources such as perceived meaning of work, job control, and social support. Background variables include occupation, age, and gender. Data were collected through web-based surveys distributed via social media and through employers. The dataset consists of a cleaned CSV file. Variables related to burnout have been recoded and reverse-coded in accordance with the applied burnout scale to ensure correct interpretation. No specialized software is required to access or use the data beyond standard programs capable of reading CSV files."@en, "Datasetet har genererats inom ett forskningsprojekt i arbetshälsovetenskap med fokus på emotionella belastningar i arbetslivet och deras samband med hälsa och välbefinnande. Datamaterialet består av enkätdata som omfattar emotionella krav, emotionellt arbete (inklusive strategin deep acting), utbrändhet och psykiskt välbefinnande, samt potentiella skyddande resurser i arbetet såsom upplevd mening i arbetet, grad av kontroll och socialt stöd. Bakgrundsvariabler inkluderar bland annat yrke, ålder och kön. Data har samlats in genom webbaserade enkäter som distribuerats via sociala medier samt genom arbetsgivare. Datasetet består av en rensad CSV-fil. Variabler relaterade till utbrändhet har omkodats och reverserats i enlighet med den använda utbrändhetsskalan för att säkerställa korrekt tolkning av skalorna. Ingen särskild programvara krävs för att använda data utöver standardprogram som kan läsa CSV-filer."@sv;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://sws.geonames.org/2661886>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.5878/w88z-ta87#distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2025-12-19T15:29:36.50902Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#landingPage> <https://doi.org/10.5878/w88z-ta87>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2025-12-19T15:29:36.50902Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Data for \"Emotional demands and burnout: differential moderating effect of job resources and age\""@en, "Data för \"Emotional demands and burnout: differential moderating effect of job resources and age\""@sv;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/SOCI>, <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/HEAL>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/temporal> _:b0__7282.
_:b0__7282 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#endDate> "2024-06"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#startDate> "2024-02"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/w88z-ta87> a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

