    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/1934a5fa0c5363446df28739590efd65>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.17044/SCILIFELAB.21904581> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021003211>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Read counts from RNAseq analysis for all 75 breast cancer samples included in the study \"Proteogenomics decodes the evolution of human ipsilateral breast cancer\". De Marchi T, Pyl PT, Sjöström M, Reinsbach SE, DiLorenzo S, Nystedt B, Tran L, Pekar G, Wärnberg F, Fredriksson I, Malmström P, Fernö M, Malmström L, Malmström J, Nimèus E.\n\n\"RNA.RAW.COUNTS\" for all genes are reported here. \"RNA.SCALED.COUNTS\" report on filtered (for missing data) reads with matching Uniprot/swissprot identifier. Reads were then scaled and centered across samples and genes.\n\nThis dataset was used for Figure 3 in the following manuscript:\n\n\"Proteogenomics decodes the evolution of human ipsilateral breast cancer\". De Marchi T, Pyl PT, Sjöström M, Reinsbach SE, DiLorenzo S, Nystedt B, Tran L, Pekar G, Wärnberg F, Fredriksson I, Malmström P, Fern�� M, Malmström L, Malmström J, Nimèus E. accepted for publication"@en;
