<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#e77e2b96e7c4aed094c58cf4b2cab3a6>.
<#e77e2b96e7c4aed094c58cf4b2cab3a6> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://doi.org/10.5878/001450>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-04-18T06:27:07.713Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#e77e2b96e7c4aed094c58cf4b2cab3a6> {
<https://doi.org/10.5878/001450> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "äldre järnålder"@sv, "Early Iron Age"@en, "folkvandringstid"@sv, "Migration Period"@en, "Societas Archaeologica Upsaliensis";
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__69713.
_:b0__69713 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/author>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/ec4ea900e9bdb6b23c549f30360fbe76>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/001450> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/SWE>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE8176053182>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Informationen i sammanfattning är hämtad ur rapporten för undersökningen:\nEn mindre boplats från slutet av äldre järnålder har undersökts vid Nedra Götala i samband med en oml��ggning av väg 32/50 mellan Vadstena och Mjölby. Boplatsens huvudfas hör till folkvandringstid men eventuellt kan det finnas ett äldre inslag från en tidigare del av äldre järnåldern, vilket representeras av ett av de två långhusen. Förutom långhusen framkom ett hundratal boplatsanläggningar i form av stolphål, härdar, gropar etc., samt ett eventuellt samtida vattenhål. Kulturlager fanns centralt på ytan och innehöll fynd av framför allt obrända djurben men även brända djurben samt lite keramik. Fynden från övriga delar av boplatsytan var mycket sparsamma. Det kunde urskiljas en viss struktur i hur boplatsytan utnyttjats för olika verksamheter. Härdarna varierade i storlek och uppbyggnad beroende på hur man velat använda dem; för att värma upp stenar, för matlagning eller någon typ av hantverk. Sammansättningen av den ved som använts visar ett relativt öppet, betat och utnyttjat landskap. Om det rör sig om en ensamgård eller inte går inte att avgöra.\n\nSyfte:\n\nInformationen i syfte är hämtad ur rapporten för undersökningen:\nUndersökningen skulle besvara frågeställningar kring lämningarnas funktion, karaktär, utbredning, datering och sammansättning. Vidare skulle eventuell förekomst av huskonstruktioner samt dessas typ fastställas.\n\nZIP-filen innehåller GIS-filer vilka innehåller information om schakt, fyndföremål, lämningstyper samt annan metadata om den arkeologiska undersökningen.\n\nData har kontinuerligt under utgrävningen förts över till Intrasis och har bearbetats vidare i GIS-miljö (ArcMap 9.3)."@sv, "GIS-material for the archaeological project: A single farm?\n\nThe ZIP file consist of GIS files with information about the excavations, findings and other metadata about the archaeological survey."@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://sws.geonames.org/2661886>, <http://sws.geonames.org/2685867>, <http://sws.geonames.org/2690959>, <http://sws.geonames.org/8127911>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.5878/001450#distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2012-12-17T00:00:00Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#landingPage> <https://doi.org/10.5878/001450>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2020-01-24T13:25:31Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "GIS-material för arkeologiskt projekt: En ensam gård? - Götala"@sv, "GIS-material for the archaeological project: A single farm? - Götala"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/EDUC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/temporal> _:b0__33131.
_:b0__33131 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#endDate> "0500"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#startDate> "0400"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/001450> a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#e6feb6678f6ef7ac13103903d060a6cf>.
<#e6feb6678f6ef7ac13103903d060a6cf> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/3adffe1051b149874c699451e6787ccf>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-04-18T06:27:07.800Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#e6feb6678f6ef7ac13103903d060a6cf> {
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/3adffe1051b149874c699451e6787ccf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "antibiotika"@sv, "antibiotikaresistens"@sv, "antibiotic resistance"@en, "antimikrobiella läkemedel"@sv, "antimicrobial drugs"@en, "folkh��lsovetenskap"@sv, "public health medicine"@en, "Vietnam"@sv, "Vietnam"@en, "låg- och medelinkomstländer"@sv, "low- and middle-income countries"@en, "antibiotics"@en, "husdjursproducenter"@sv, "livestock farmers"@en, "djurläkemedel"@sv, "veterinary drugs"@en, "veterinärtjänst"@sv, "veterinary treatment"@en, "veterinära läkemedelsbutiker"@sv, "veterinary drug shops"@en, "veterinära apotek"@sv, "veterinary pharmacies"@en, "Antibiotikaförsäljning"@sv, "Antibiotic sales"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__24064.
_:b0__24064 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/4162b6d684a8774ee9eb3cac63d8c45b>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/3adffe1051b149874c699451e6787ccf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__63885.
_:b0__63885 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/63ba57b8a79edace37f4269876b0f249>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/3adffe1051b149874c699451e6787ccf> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/NON_PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002817>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Antibiotikaanvändning inom djurproduktionen är omfattande globalt och det är allmänt vedertaget att antibiotikaanvändning och resistensutveckling är tätt sammankopplade. I många låg- och medelinkomstländer säljs antibiotika utan recept till bönder, som därmed till stor del är beroende av försäljarens kunskap och råd kring behandling. För att få en ökad förståelse för försäljarnas påverkan på antibiotikaanvändningen på gårdsnivå i Vietnam genomfördes en enkätbaserad studie bland 50 försäljare i veterinära läkemedelsbutiker i Thai Nguyen-provinsen i norra Vietnam.\n\nEnkäten innehöll 44 frågor inom ett antal olika områden, som rutiner och rådgivning vid försäljning av antibiotika, och kunskap om antibiotika och resistens.\n\nDatasetet innehåller 129 kolumner och 52 rader. Variabelnamn i datasetet är förkortade och svarsalternativen kodade. En kodnyckel för svarsalternativen finns tillgänglig i en separat fil, ”Veterinary_drug_shops_Vietnam_2024_explanations”. Frågeformuläret finns i ”Veterinary_drug_shops_Vietnam_2024_questionnaire”."@sv, "Antibiotic use in livestock production is extensive globally, and it is generally accepted that antibiotic use is closely linked to the development of antimicrobial resistance. In many low- and middle-income countries, antibiotics are sold to farmers over-the-counter, who then become very dependent on the salesperson’s knowledge and advice regarding the treatment. To increase the understanding of the salespersons’ impact on antibiotic use in livestock farms in Vietnam, a survey-based study was performed among 50 veterinary drug shop workers in Thai Nguyen province in northern Vietnam.\n\nThe questionnaire contained 44 questions covering several aspects, such as routines and advice when selling antibiotics, as well as knowledge about antibiotics and resistance. \n\nThe dataset consists of 129 columns and 52 rows. Variable names and answers are coded, and explanations can be found in a separate file, ”Veterinary_drug_shops_Vietnam_2024_explanations”. The questionnaire can be found in the file ”Veterinary_drug_shops_Vietnam_2024_questionnaire”."@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://sws.geonames.org/1562822>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#contactPoint> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/51114b511532c3a2185d2769d45f9a7f>, <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/8cedc64d4f8c0d330584d1af8de2b756>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2024-07-22T12:15:43.029137Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2024-07-22T12:20:50.608998Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Praktik och kunskap relaterad till antibiotika och antibiotikaresistens bland försäljare i veterinära läkemedelsbutiker i Vietnam"@sv, "Practices and knowledge related to antibiotics and antimicrobial resistance among Vietnamese veterinary drug shop workers"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/HEAL>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/temporal> _:b0__80300.
_:b0__80300 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#endDate> "2023-03-01"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#startDate> "2023-02-20"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime>
}

<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#ea4f78f4e98329607328a12119a8399c>.
<#ea4f78f4e98329607328a12119a8399c> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://doi.org/10.5878/esy1-jh90>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-04-18T06:27:07.821Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#ea4f78f4e98329607328a12119a8399c> {
<https://doi.org/10.5878/esy1-jh90> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Noise"@en, "Buller"@sv, "Skolor"@sv, "Schools"@en, "Vibration"@sv, "Vibration"@en, "Akustik"@sv, "Acoustics"@en, "Förskolebarn"@sv, "Child, Preschool"@en, "Byggnadsdesign och konstruktion"@sv, "Facility Design and Construction"@en, "förskoleundervisning"@sv, "preschool education"@en, "ljudmiljö"@sv, "acoustic environment"@en, "förskolan"@sv, "preschool"@en, "socioekonomiska faktorer"@sv, "socioeconomic factors"@en, "undervisningslokaler"@sv, "teaching premises"@en, "Rumsakustik"@sv, "Room acoustics"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__19852.
_:b0__19852 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/3828130811a6343df9c9d6b88c1580f5>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/esy1-jh90> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__17087.
_:b0__17087 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/839e95dba7b7a8dc191c1c9b4744a77e>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/esy1-jh90> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021003153>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Datasetet innehåller resultatet av rumsakustiska mätningar från 57 förskolerum i kommunalt drivna förskolor i Göteborg. Mätningarna gjordes under 2019-2020. Utförligare information återfinns i den engelska katalogposten under \"Description\".\n\nTabulärdatan tillhandahålls i .xlsx- och semikolonseparerat .csv-format.\n\nSe den engelska katalogposten med beskrivningen av datasetet samt dokumentationsfilen för variabelbeskrivningar."@sv, "The data set contains the results of room acoustic measurements and additional information from 57 rooms in 19 different public preschools in the Gothenburg area (Sweden). The measurements were conducted during 2019-2020. Children at preschool are divided into units commonly, but not always, based on age. The presented data covers in total 31 different units aimed at older children. Up to three rooms per unit were measured, focusing on the main play rooms and the meal room. In cases where these rooms were the same, only one room per unit was measured.\n\nThe preschools are divided into three groups, strata, based on the year when they were built: 1980-1994, 1995-2006, and 2007-2018.\n\nTo reach an even distribution within each strata with respect to socioeconomic factors, we used an existing preschool-specific index acquired from the central preschool administration [Jorsäter, M., Resursfördelningsmodell Göteborg 2019. 2019, Statistics Sweden (SCB)] (attached as a PDF file).  The index is based on a model from Statistics Sweden (SCB) where school performance after elementary school is linked with a number of explanatory variables related to the socioeconomic background of the individual child and her/his parents. When these factors are known for the children at a specific preschool, an averaged index is calculated, centered around 100. Preschools with an index over 100 have a larger share of children with a risk of not qualifying for high school (gymnasium). Preschools with an index less than 100 have a smaller share of children with a risk of not qualifying for high school. The purpose of the index is to prioritize economic support to school units with the highest need and increase equity. \n\nRoom acoustic parameters and unoccupied noise levels were measured in each room using a laptop and an external 8-channel sound card (HEAD acoustics SQuadriga II). An omnidirectional sound source with a built-in generation of pink noise (50-20000 Hz) was used to excite the room. A modification was made to the device in order to extract the electronic signal from the loudspeaker.\n\nUnoccupied noise levels were measured in accordance with ISO 16032:2004. In some rooms the contribution from the ventilation could be estimated by conducting the measurements with the ventilation unit turned on and off separately.\n\nRoom acoustic measurements were conducted following the precision method in ISO 3382-2:2008. Three microphones were used simultaneously with predetermined height intervals (1±0.2, 1.4±0.2, 1.6±0.2). The standard’s recommendation to use natural source positions was implemented by placing the loudspeaker where we estimated that a child would have its head during sitting and standing activities in the room. In addition, a corner position was always used. Impulse responses were calculated by the software ArtemiS SUITE using the loudspeaker's extracted electronic signal as the reference.\n\nImpulse responses and unoccupied sound pressure level spectra were exported to Matlab. Octave band room acoustic parameters were calculated for 125 – 8000 Hz from the impulse responses with the ITA-toolbox 8.6 [Berzborn, M., et al., The ITA-Toolbox: An Open Source MATLAB Toolbox for Acoustic Measurements and Signal Processing, in DAGA 2017. 2017: Kiel.]. The analysis was done for reverberation time T20 and EDT (Early decay time), and Speech Clarity, C50. An addition to the code was made to evaluate the Clarity index with a shorter time, C35, which uses 35 ms instead of the default 50 ms as suggested by Whitlock and Dodd [Whitlock, J.A.T. and G. Dodd, Speech Intelligibility in Classrooms: Specific Acoustical Needs for Primary School Children. Building Acoustics, 2008. 15(1): p. 35-47.]\n\nSound strength, G (dB), was calculated from the sound power of the loudspeaker LW (measured according to the ISO 3741 standard) and the resulting sound pressure level Lp in a measurement point: G=Lp - LW + 31 [SS-EN ISO 3382-1:2009].\n\n\nAdditional information collected during the measurements:\nDimensions and shape of the room\nThe floor and wall type of construction material is classified into heavy or lightweight\nA subjective evaluation of the degree of furnishing and categorized as sparse, normal or dense. \nMaterial type of the acoustic treatment in the ceiling: porous type (typical white mineral wool) or other various types, e.g. perforated gypsum boards\nSound absorption on the walls* and their approximate total area\n\n*The concept wall absorption is interpreted as a fabric or porous material mounted on, or in the vicinity of a wall and which was subjectively judged as acoustically absorbing.\n\nThe data set consists of seven spreadsheet files where each row contains data from one preschool room. Each preschool room is identified with 4 numbers: \nROOM_ID1: Represents building year interval: \n“1”=1980-1994, “2”=1995-2006, “3”=2007-2018 \nROOM_ID2: Represents the number of the preschool within each building year interval\nROOM_ID3: Represents the unit number within each preschool\nROOM_ID4: Represents the room number within each unit\n\nMissing data is indicated with an empty cell.\n\nThe data is also available as semicolon-separated .csv files.\n\n--- --- ---\n\nXLSX-file “INFO”\nSES = Socioeconomic index of preschool\nVolume = Volume of room in (m3) \nFloorA = Floor area (m2)\nHeight_min / Height_max = height to inner ceiling (m)\nFurnDeg = Subjective furnishing degree, 1 = spares, 2 = normal, 3 = dense\nFloorConst = Floor construction, 1 = lighweight, 2 = heavy (concrete)\nWallConst = Wall construction, 1 = lightweight, 2 = heavy, 3= mixed\nCeilingAbs = Acoustic ceiling, 1 = porous (mineral wool), 2 = other (commonly perforated boards)\nwallAbs = Amount of wall absorbers (m2)\n--- --- ---\n\nMeasured room acoustic parameters are presented as room-averaged for the three different microphone heights separately: low = 1±0.2, mid = 1.4±0.2 and high = 1.6±0.2 m and for the octave bands from 125 Hz to 8000 Hz:\n\nXLSX-file “T20”\nReverberation time T20 (s)\n\nXLSX-file “EDT”\nEarly decay time (s)\n\nXLSX-file “G”\nSound strength (dB)\n\nXLSX-file “C50”\nSpeech Clarity (dB)\n\nXLSX-file “C35”\nSpeech Clarity with integration time 35 ms (dB)\n--- --- ---\n\nMeasured unoccupied noise levels are presented as Leq (equivalent) levels in 1/3 octave bands from 25 Hz to 10000 Hz in the spreadsheet file “BKG.xlsx”. For some rooms there is also an estimated contribution from the ventilation system to the background noise equivalent level. \n\nXLSX-file “BKG”\nEquivalent level (dB)\n--- --- ---"@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://sws.geonames.org/2711533>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#contactPoint> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/176d4e769595305d6b17eb1960ae120b>, <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/898549019fcf9f49d62c1fb5a4e0676a>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.5878/esy1-jh90#distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2023-10-30T10:59:23.525404Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#landingPage> <https://doi.org/10.5878/esy1-jh90>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2023-10-30T11:11:09.523004Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Förskolerum och rumsakustik - insamlat och analyserat data i forskningsprojektet SPACE (Supportive Preschool AcoustiC Environment)"@sv, "Preschool room acoustics - collected and analysed data in the research project SPACE (Supportive Preschool AcoustiC Environment)"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/HEAL>, <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/TECH>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#b1cb24116b3b2f3257e99b89db5a600c>.
<#b1cb24116b3b2f3257e99b89db5a600c> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://doi.org/10.5878/y68g-4v67>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-04-18T06:27:07.837Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#b1cb24116b3b2f3257e99b89db5a600c> {
<https://doi.org/10.5878/y68g-4v67> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Antarktis"@sv, "Antarctica"@en, "Antarctic region"@en, "Första svenska Antarktisexpeditionen, 1901-1904"@sv, "Swedish Antarctic Expedition, 1901-1904"@en, "Nordenskjöld, Otto, 1869-1928"@sv, "Nordenskjöld, Otto, 1869-1928"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__93813.
_:b0__93813 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/3c73de3c9cede65212391cc3a208bb85>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/y68g-4v67> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__17440.
_:b0__17440 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/8cf542f0e17d58f88cb781151a1d042d>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/y68g-4v67> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021003153>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Syftet med forskningsprojektet var att dokumentera lämningarna efter Otto Nordenskjölds Antarktisexpeditionen 1901-1903. Materialet best��r av fotografier, planer, ritningar, 3d-modeller och drönarfilmer från Snow Hillön, Hoppets Vik och Seymourön.\n\nDenna katalogpost samlar de ritningar och planer som skapades på Snow Hillön.\n\nSe den engelska beskrivningen för mer information.\n\nRitningarna av vinterstationen skapades med hjälp av traditionella metoder och är tillgängliga både som originalskisser med noteringar och renritade i bläck. Planerna är skapade med hjälp av den skanningsdata som samlades in på den tolfte, trettonde och nittonde januari med en Faro Focus m70 skanner."@sv, "The first Swedish Antarctic Expedition (1901-1903), led by Otto Nordenskjöld, sailed to Antarctica on the ship Antarctic captained by CA Larsen, and established a research station on Snow Hill Island. There six members overwintered and performed paleontological, meteorological, geomagnetic and geological studies, while the rest of the expedition set sail for South Orkney.\n\nAfter the winter, on the way back to Snow Hill Island, the Antarctic got stuck in the ice and sank. At this point, the expedition members were divided into three groups. One of these overwintered an extra year on Snow Hill Island, whereas the other two groups were forced to build stone huts in order to overwinter at Hope Bay and Paulet Island. An Argentinean vessel, the Corbeta Uruguay, rescued the expedition in November 1903.\n\nCHAQ 2020 is an Argentinean-Swedish project with fieldwork in the area around the Antarctic Peninsula aiming to investigating and documenting the historical remains of the first Swedish South Polar expedition under the leadership of Otto Nordenskjöld 1901-1903. The material was collected in January and February 2020. \n\nThis catalogue entry collects the drawings and plans created from data gathered at Snow Hill Island.\n\nThe drawings of the winter station were carried out using traditional methods and are available both as pencil originals with notes and cleaned up ink drawings. The plans were produced using scan data from the Faro Focus m70 on January 12, 13, and 19."@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://sws.geonames.org/6697173>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#contactPoint> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/9ecfb5d4fd4d2df193946adae693a4ca>, <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/5378deb8171ad25b3b2adbe96d9b9054>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.5878/y68g-4v67#distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2021-03-02T08:01:44.857047Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#landingPage> <https://doi.org/10.5878/y68g-4v67>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2021-09-02T13:29:55.050197Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "CHAQ2020 - Snow Hillön - Planer och ritningar"@sv, "CHAQ2020 - Snow Hill Island - Plans and drawings"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/EDUC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/temporal> _:b0__98005.
_:b0__98005 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#endDate> "2099"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#startDate> "1900"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime>
}

<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#4d7f717a157d6c4adc10c545ebd50da2>.
<#4d7f717a157d6c4adc10c545ebd50da2> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://doi.org/10.5878/001865>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-04-18T06:27:07.882Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#4d7f717a157d6c4adc10c545ebd50da2> {
<https://doi.org/10.5878/001865> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "historisk tid"@sv, "historical period"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__84157.
_:b0__84157 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/author>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/2469056885632d0db509178609fcbd26>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/001865> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/SWE>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002932>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The ZIP file consist of GIS files and an Access database with information about the excavations, findings and other metadata about the archaeological survey."@en, "Informationen i sammanfattning är hämtad ur rapporten för undersökningen:\nRiksantikvarieämbetet UV Öst har utfört en arkeologisk utredning, etapp 1 och 2 utmed sträckan Södra Freberga-Sjöhamra m fl omkring 3 kilometer sydväst om Motala, i Västra Stenby, Vinnerstads och Motala socknar, Motala kommun, Östergötland. Utredningen föranleddes av planerade schaktningsarbeten i samband med förläggande av ny jordkabel i området. Utredning, etapp 1, innebar studier av arkiv och kartor, samt en fältbesiktning av kabelsträckan. Utredning, etapp 2 utfördes i form av sökschaktsgrävning med hjälp av grävmaskin under september 2006. En av de undersökta sträckorna inneh��ll en raserad husgrund, RAÄ 220, som sannolikt kan härledas till Södra Kullas by- eller gårdstomt.\n\nSyfte:\n\nInformationen i syfte är hämtad ur rapporten för undersökningen:\nSyftet med utredningen var att fastställa om lagskyddade fornlämningar var belägna inom kabelförläggningens sträckning och att om möjligt undvika att fast fornlämning berördes av arbetsföretaget.\n\nZIP-filen innehåller GIS-filer samt en Access datafil vilka innehåller information om schakt, fyndföremål, lämningstyper samt annan metadata om den arkeologiska undersökningen."@sv;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://sws.geonames.org/2661886>, <http://sws.geonames.org/2690959>, <http://sws.geonames.org/8126530>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.5878/001865#distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2014-04-17T00:00:00Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#landingPage> <https://doi.org/10.5878/001865>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2016-07-08T08:39:22Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "GIS-material för arkeologiskt projekt: Husgrund vid Södra Kulla gård - Södra Fredberga"@sv, "GIS-material for the archaeological project: House foundation at Södra Kulla farmstead - Södra Fredberga"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/EDUC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/temporal> _:b0__38379.
_:b0__38379 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#endDate> "2000"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#startDate> "1050"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/001865> a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#7f658dcb18f8b143ec331ddfd02629da>.
<#7f658dcb18f8b143ec331ddfd02629da> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://doi.org/10.5878/001777>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-04-18T06:27:07.894Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#7f658dcb18f8b143ec331ddfd02629da> {
<https://doi.org/10.5878/001777> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "järnålder"@sv, "Iron Age"@en, "bronsålder"@sv, "Bronze Age"@en, "stenålder"@sv, "stone age"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__26825.
_:b0__26825 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/author>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/2469056885632d0db509178609fcbd26>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/001777> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/SWE>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002932>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Informationen i sammanfattning är hämtad ur rapporten för undersökningen:\nInför detaljplanering för nya bensinstationer i NV Tornby, Linköpings kommun, har Riksantikvarieämbetet UV Öst utfört en arkeologisk utredning, etapp 2. På en västsluttning utmed en svag förhöjning i områdets SÖ del påträffades 9 förhistoriska anläggningar i form av härdar eller gravar, stolphål och kulturlager. Rikligt med skärvsten, sot och kol påträffades i flera av dem. Anläggningarna har ytundersökts men inte grävts bort. Ett par fynd av brända ben och bearbetad kvarts gjordes. Området där förhistoriska anläggningar påträffades har avgränsats. På området i övrigt påträffades inga förhistoriska anläggningar.\n\nSyfte:\n\nInformationen i syfte är hämtad ur rapporten för undersökningen:\nSyftet med utredningen var att avgöra om området innehåller lagskyddade fornlämningar.\n\nZIP-filen innehåller GIS-filer samt en Access datafil vilka innehåller information om schakt, fyndföremål, lämningstyper samt annan metadata om den arkeologiska undersökningen."@sv, "The information in the abstract is translated from the archaeological report:\nDue to local plans concerning new petrol stations in northwest Tornby, Linköping municipality, the Swedish National Heritage Board's Contract Archaeology Division, UV Öst has performed an assessment, phase 2. Along a stretch of somewhat higher ground sloping slightly to the west, in the south-east part of the area, nine prehistoric features were found, such as hearths or graves, post holes and cultural layers. Several of the features contained great amounts of fire cracked stones, soot and charcoal. The features have been examined on the surface but not excavated. A few finds of burnt bones and worked quartz were also made. The area containing archaeological remains has been delimited. No archaeological remnants were found in the rest of the area.\n\nPurpose:\n\nThe information in the purpose is translated from the archaeological report:\nThe purpose of the archaeological assessment was to determine if the area contains any archaeological remains protected by law.\n\nThe ZIP file consist of GIS files and an Access database with information about the excavations, findings and other metadata about the archaeological survey."@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://sws.geonames.org/2661886>, <http://sws.geonames.org/2694759>, <http://sws.geonames.org/8126430>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.5878/001777#distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2014-04-10T00:00:00Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#landingPage> <https://doi.org/10.5878/001777>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2016-07-07T10:16:16Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "GIS-material för arkeologiskt projekt: Nya lämningar vid Bergsvägen - Ny detaljplan g��llande bensinstationer"@sv, "GIS-material for the archaeological project: New remains by Bergsvägen - New local plan for petrol stations"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/EDUC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/temporal> _:b0__13280.
_:b0__13280 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#endDate> "1050"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#startDate> "-8199"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/001777> a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

